-- SKS to Sell Shares From July 28 in India's First Microfinance Public Offer
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-07-12T05:54:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/sks-microfinance-to-sell-shares-in-ipo-july-28-to-july-30-document-shows.html

          
          
             SKS Microfinance Ltd., Indiaâ€™s
largest microfinance company, plans to sell shares in its $250
million initial public offering from July 28 to July 30,
according to a sale document obtained by Bloomberg.   
 The company plans to set the price range at which it will
offer the shares on July 26, according to the term sheet.    
 Citigroup Inc., Credit Suisse Group AG and Kotak Mahindra
Capital Co. are managing the sale, the Hyderabad-based company
said in its draft prospectus to the capital markets regulator in
March.  
